Moneys in the fund shall be allocated as follows:
The Department of Parks shall receive ten percent (10%);
The Department of Fish and Wildlife Resources shall receive ten percent (10%);
The Energy and Environment Cabinet, Division of Forestry, shall receive ten percent (10%);
Ten percent (10%) shall be allocated for wild rivers corridors established by the Kentucky Wild Rivers Act, KRS 146.200 to 146.360, and any administrative regulations promulgated pursuant thereto;
The Nature Preserves Commission shall receive ten percent (10%); and
The board shall receive the remaining fifty percent (50%), for allocation to private, nonprofit land trust organizations, state agencies, local governments, and state colleges and universities. Any funds expended under this paragraph to private, nonprofit land trust organizations shall be matched dollar-for-dollar as required in KRS 146.560(2).
